\int_0^\infty \dfrac{dx}{1+x^4}
\int_0^\infty \dfrac{u^{p-1}}{1+u} du = \dfrac{\pi}{\sin( \pi p)}
p
u = x^4
du = 4x^3 dx
p
u=x^4
du=4x^3 dx
dx = \frac{1}{4x^3} du = \frac{1}{4{(x^4)}^{3/4}} du =  \frac{1}{4{u}^{3/4}} du
\int_0^\infty \dfrac{dx}{1+x^4} = \frac{1}{4}\int_0^\infty \frac{u^{-3/4}du}{1+u} = \frac{\pi}{4\sin(\pi/4)}=\frac{\pi }{2 \sqrt{2}}
